<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Granic Meets With Izetbegovic at Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Granic Meets With Izetbegovic at Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705190994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1700 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705190994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Mate Granic, deputy prime minister and foreign 
minister, met Bosnian President Alija Izetbegovic at Zagreb 
airport this afternoon. President Izetbegovic is on a stopover 
in Zagreb on his way to Saudi Arabia where he will be taking 
part in the pilgrimage to Mecca with 400 other Muslims from 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia. We discussed the implementation 
of the Vienna agreement, President Tudjman's visit to Sarajevo 
-- which is expected to take place very soon -- as well as 
various forms of cooperation between Bosnia-Herzegovina and 
Croatia, such as transport, trade and the power industry, 
President Izetbegovic said after the talks. 
  Minister Granic said that there were no longer any obstacles 
in the way of President Tudjman's visit to Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
He added that the exact date of the visit would be determined 
in a couple of days. Minister Granic said that the talks also 
centered on cooperation between Bosnia-Herzegovina and Croatia 
in the area of trade, as well as a joint approach to European 
integration, the system of security and succession. As far as 
the Washington and Vienna agreements are concerned, both sides 
have agreed that their implementation should be ensured as soon 
as possible, Minister Granic said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

