<H3> <TI>   MKDH: No Secret Agreement With Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MKDH: No Secret Agreement With Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705164794 Bratislava Slovak Radio Network in Hungarian 
1300 GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1705164794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Slovak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] No secret agreement whatsoever exists between the 
coalition government and the Hungarian parliamentary parties in 
Slovakia. This was stated at a press briefing of the Hungarian 
Christian Democratic Movement [MKDH] by Pal Csaky today. 
  Speaking about the forthcoming parliamentary elections, he 
said that the MKDH supported the notion that the Hungarian 
political forces in Slovakia ought to have a joint stand, but he 
did not agree with the idea of establishing a joint party. The 
MKDH wishes to study the proposal of a union worked out by 
Coexistence, but, for the time being, it is supporting the idea 
of creating a tripartite coalition between MKDH-Coexistence and 
the Hungarian Civic Party. 
  Csaky also said that, after the elections, his party will 
support any government that, on the basis of democratic 
principles, continues on the course Slovakia has entered on. 

</TEXT>

