<H3> <TI>   Crvenkovski, Karayalcin Hold News Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crvenkovski, Karayalcin Hold News Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1805110294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2110 
GMT 17 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1805110294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy prime 
minister, who is holding contacts in Skopje, the capital of The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM], has held a joint 
news conference with FYROM Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski. 
  Speaking at the news conference, Karayalcin said that the 
relations between the socialists and the social democrats in the 
Balkan countries are very important, adding that these relations 
will, at the same time, contribute to regional peace. Pointing 
to the importance of historic ties of friendship with Macedonia, 
Karayalcin said that there are many Macedonians in Turkey and 
that they are engaged in successful work. Noting that during 
his contacts in the FYROM developments in the Balkan region and 
existing areas of cooperation were discussed, Karayalcin added 
that Turkey will send corn to the FYROM. He recalled that a 
$25,000 [as heard] loan agreement through Eximbank was signed 
between the two countries, adding that this loan will be 
extended in September or October. 
  Crvenkovski, also speaking at the news conference, gave 
details on his meetings with Karayalcin. He stressed that an 
agreement has been reached on the continuation of the existing 
relations. Crvenkovski added that his country received a lot of 
support from Turkey during its difficult periods. 
  Karayalcin attended a dinner in his honor hosted by 
Crvenkovski this evening. He also visited the Turkish Embassy 
in Skopje. He will return to Turkey tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

