<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brcko, May 17 (TANJUG) -- Bosnian Moslem and Croat 
forces on Tuesday attacked Bosnian Serb positions in an attempt 
to cut off the Serb land corridor in the Posavina region near 
Brcko in northern Bosnia. Around 15:00 hours local time on 
Tuesday, Moslem forces fired 15 82-mm shells on Serb positions 
in Begovaca in the Brcko area, Bosnian Serb army sources said in 
a statement. The Bosnian Serb army did not return fire, it said. 
  Croat units in Orasje, Posavina, opened fire from 
anti-aircraft machine guns and anti-tank weapons on Serb 
settlements of Lesnici and Jenjici, the statement said, adding 
that the Serb side again did not return fire. Croatian and 
especially Moslem forces have massed heavily armed units around 
Brcko, a town which is situated in the narrowest part of the 
Serb land corridor linking the eastern and western parts of the 
Bosnian Serb republic. Moslem and Croat military commanders 
have announced an offensive on this part of the Serb corridor. 
  Earlier this month, Moslem forces launched artillery attacks 
on central Brcko, killing four civilians and wounding 15, which 
was confirmed by monitors of the United Nations Protection Force 
(UNPROFOR). 

</TEXT>

