<F P=106> [Article by "ajk": "According to Devaty, BIS Still Needs </F>
Former StB Agents"] 
  [Text] Prague--Approximately 5 percent of the employees at 
the Security Information Service [BIS] are former State Security 
[StB] agents. Stanislav Devaty, acting director of the secret 
service, said at the meeting with the members of the Defense and 
Security Committee of the Chamber yesterday that, although he is 
not completely satisfied with BIS personnel, the office 
continues to use the expert knowledge of some agents of the 
communist secret police. 
  "I employ them because they are experts particularly on 
intelligence technology and are therefore qualified to provide 
training for new employees," Devaty explained and added that not 
a single one of them worked at the StB in the Department for 
Combating the Internal Enemy. 
  Devaty illustrated this by the example of one of the top men 
in the BIS Economic Department who accompanied him yesterday to 
the parliament. 
  Devaty also informed the deputies that BIS spent 489 million 
korunas [Kc] from the State Treasury last year. 

</TEXT>

