  [Excerpts] Czech Cabinet ministers held a meeting today. 
Ales Hermanek reports. 
  [Hermanek] [passage omitted] Prime Minister Klaus expressed 
his disappointment with regard to the progress of talks on 
Russia's debts to the Czech Republic. He said that the 
accommodating attitude the Russian prime minister demonstrated 
with regard to this problem during Klaus's recent visit to 
Russia had not been reflected in concrete deeds by Russian 
Government officials. Because the deadline of 30 May, when the 
methods of debt repayment were due to be resolved, is 
threatened, Prime Minister Klaus plans to telephone Russian 
Prime Minister Chernomyrdin on 18 May and agree on further and 
more vigorous action with him. 

