<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berisha, Rugova on `Grave Situation' in Kosovo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berisha, Rugova on `Grave Situation' in Kosovo </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1705111294 Tirana ATA in English 0812 GMT 17 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1705111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 17 (ATA) -- President Sali Berisha met 
on May 16 with president of Kosova Ibrahim Rugova. They 
discussed the conditions in which the Albanian nation is at 
present, the grave situation in Kosova and the development of 
democratic reforms in Albania, the President's Press and 
Information Office reports. 
  Both presidents were of the opinion that the establishment 
of 
dialogue between Prishtina and Belgrade, in the presence of a 
third party is imperative for the measures to normalize the life 
and for a political solution of the Kosova issue. 
  They pointed out that the stability and the independence of 
Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia] are 
important for the peace and stability of Albanians and other 
nationalities of the Balkans. They encourage the Albanian 
political forces to cooperate with each other for the 
consolidation of the stability of the Macedonian Republic as 
well as for a guarantee of the human rights and freedoms of the 
Albanians as a condition for the stability of this republic. 
The meeting was conducted in a spirit of full understanding. 

</TEXT>

