<H3> <TI>   Ministry Welcomes Greek Response to Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Welcomes Greek Response to Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1705111494 Tirana ATA in English 1010 GMT 17 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1705111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Statement of the Spokesman for the Albanian Foreign </F>
Ministry" -- ATA headline] 
  [Text] Tirana, May 17 (ATA) -- A report by the spokesman 
for the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Albania 
issued on May 16 says that the Albanian Foreign Ministry 
expresses the satisfaction for the fact that the Albanian 
proposal for a forthcoming Albanian-Greek meeting in Tirana, has 
had a positive response from the Greek foreign minister, 
Papoulias. The report adds that the freedom and the rights of 
the Greek minority in Albania are and will be guaranteed and 
invulnerable. This reality of the Greek minority in Albania has 
been acknowledged and esteemed by relevant international 
organizations as well. 
  The Albanian deputy foreign minister, Arjan Starova, had a 
meeting on May 13 with the ambassador of the Greek Republic in 
Tirana, Mr. Tsalikis. He forwarded the Albanian proposal for a 
meeting in Tirana between the foreign ministers of the two 
countries. Such an idea was expressed some days ago by the 
president of Albania, Sali Berisha, in an interview with the 
Albanian Radio and Television at the end of his visit to Romania 
last week. 

</TEXT>

