<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Selami Meets With FYROM Party Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Selami Meets With FYROM Party Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605093094 Tirana ATA in English 0808 GMT 16 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1605093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 16 (ATA) -- Chairman of the Democratic 
Party of Albania Eduard Selami met yesterday with the chairman 
of the Party for Democratic Prosperity, Arben Djaferi [title as 
received]. They evaluated the relations and cooperation 
existing between the two parties they represent. Mr. Djaferi 
acquainted Mr. Selami with the efforts of this party for the 
extension and guaranteeing of the national and human rights of 
the Albanians in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM]. 
  Mr. Selami stressed that the constructive and resolute stand 
of the Party for Democratic Prosperity towards the stability of 
Macedonia and towards the extension and realisation of the 
rights of the Albanians in Macedonia, as a condition for the 
stability, have a particular importance. He considered as 
significant the cooperation and coordination of the actions of 
all Albanian political forces in Macedonia for a joint program 
with regard to the realisation of the Albanians' demands and the 
independence and stability of the Macedonian state. 
  Concerning the census, Mr. Selami said it is an important 
act 
which should be conducted according to the criteria defined by 
the experts' commission of the Council of Europe. 

</TEXT>

