<H3> <TI>   Pittner Not Planning `Extra Measures' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pittner Not Planning `Extra Measures' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1605200694 Prague CTK in English 1420 GMT 16 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1605200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava May 16 (CTK) -- The Slovak Police do not 
prepare "any extra measures" in connection with the envisaged 
visit by Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of Russia's Liberal 
Democratic Party (LDPR), to Slovakia, Slovak Interior Minister 
Ladislav Pittner told CTK today. Zhirinovskiy is to arrive for 
a private visit to Bratislava on May 21, at the invitation of 
Ladislav Mojzis, the owner of West-Club restaurant in 
Bratislava, and Jozef Lauko, who attended the LDPR April 
congress as an honorary guest. 
  Any Russian citizen can arrive in Slovakia when invited, as 
Slovakia has visa-free relations with Russia, Pittner said. 
"The situation would be different if the visitor did not keep 
to Slovak laws," Pittner said, adding that in this case police 
would act according to the law. 

</TEXT>

