<H3> <TI>   Five Romany Parties To Contest Election Jointly </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Five Romany Parties To Contest Election Jointly </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805120594 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 16 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1805120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "Romanies Jointly"] </F>
  [Text] Kosice--An agreement on joint entry into the 
elections was signed in Kosice yesterday by representatives of 
the five largest Romany parties and movements from east and 
central Slovakia. In concluding the agreement, the chairmen of 
the Romany Congress, the Romany Civic Initiative, the Union of 
the Romany Civic Initiative, the Romany Party of Social 
Democracy, and the Party of Integration of Romanies proceeded 
from their parties' failure in the last elections, which was 
caused by their own fragmentation. There are at present eight 
political parties and 12 cultural associations of Romanies in 
Slovakia associating almost 90 percent of the 520,000 Romanies, 
most of whom live in eastern Slovakia. According to the parties 
to the agreement, they also contemplate joining an electoral 
coalition but have not yet decided on a partner. 

</TEXT>

