<F P=102>   AU1805122494 Bratislava PRAVDA in Slovak 16 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1805122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "...And They Set Up a New Party"] </F>
  [Excerpts] Bratislava--"Forces that do not wish for a 
strong green party on the Slovak political scene have become 
active again," states a statement issued by the Green Party in 
Slovakia (SZS), which SZS Deputy Chairman Pavol Fabian made 
available to the TA SR yesterday. Three party members decided 
to leave the SZS before the coming elections and have launched a 
petition campaign, the aim of which is to register the 
"genuinely Slovak Green Party." One of the founders of the new 
party is a former SZS member, who was recently caught as she 
unlawfully manipulated the registration cards of SZS members. 
[passage omitted] Only 17 days after this incident, she set up 
the new party. According to the SZS Presidium, the three 
signatories of the appeal for the establishment of the new party 
distinguished themselves by minimal activism in protecting the 
environment, and their departure represents no loss for the SZS 
from this viewpoint. 

</TEXT>

