<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Rejects Resignation Rumors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Rejects Resignation Rumors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805161194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1500 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805161194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Croatian Government has not resigned and will 
not resign despite [break in transmission] as Prime Minister 
Nikica Valentic began today's government session. Nenad Stazic 
has the report. 
  [Stazic] The government has displayed a principled and 
responsible approach to its duties over the past 14 months. It 
is still a factor of stability, so the prime minister and the 
government in general will not do anything to destabilize the 
situation in Croatia. What fuelled yesterday's rumors about the 
government's possible resignation was the decision to drop items 
from the agenda of the House of Counties -- which was not the 
most ingenious solution -- so the government will not propose 
that any items be dropped from the agenda of the Chamber of 
Representatives [break in transmission]. 

</TEXT>

