<DOCNO> FBIS4-55663 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu097_k_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-097 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tudjman in Talks with Owen, Stoltenberg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tudjman in Talks with Owen, Stoltenberg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805204194 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2000 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman today received 
international mediators Thorvald Stoltenberg and Lord David 
Owen. The talks were attended by Croatian Foreign Minister Mate 
Granic and Defense Minister Gojko Susak. Under discussion was 
the continuation of talks between the Croatian Government and 
local Serb representatives on the reintegration of the 
UN-protected areas into the Croatian constitutional system. 
After the talks, Thorvald Stoltenberg said he hopes the next 
round of talks, which is to deal with economic issues, will be 
called soon. Lord Owen said the mediators acquainted President 
Tudjman with the results of this morning's talks with Serbian 
President Milosevic and Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic in 
Belgrade. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

