  [Text] Croatian President Franjo Tudjman received a letter 
from Bosnian Presidency President Alija Izetbegovic, who stayed 
in Zagreb yesterday en route to Saudi Arabia, the presidential 
office reports. I want to send you my regards and confirm the 
commitment of the Presidency and Government of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to the spirit and provisions of the Vienna 
agreement. We shall do our best to implement this agreement as 
purposefully as possible [break in transmission] Awaiting your 
forthcoming visit to Sarajevo, I would like to express my kind 
regards, Alija Izetbegovic writes in his letter to President 
Tudjman. 

