<H3> <TI>   Government Reviews Results of Economic Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Reviews Results of Economic Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805161394 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1805161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] At a session chaired by Mirko Marjanovic, the 
Government of the Republic of Serbia concluded that the stable 
conditions for economic activity have been successfully 
maintained in the three and a half months since the beginning of 
the implementation of the economic program. The exchange rate 
of the dinar is unchanged and is accompanied by a gradual 
increase in foreign exchange reserves and industrial output, 
which was up 2.7 percent in April. 
  The deficit in the republican budget is being reduced, as is 
total public expenditure. Average wages and other earnings have 
increased in real terms. In the first two weeks of May there 
was a slight increase in retail prices and the prices of 
agricultural products at vegetable markets. 
  Accepting the report on the results achieved in the 
implementation of the program of reconstruction of the monetary 
system and the strategy of economic recovery of Yugoslavia, the 
government concluded that the faster adaptation of companies and 
banks to the requirements of the market, the strengthening of 
financial discipline and legal security, the elimination of 
illegal financial transactions, and the rationalization in the 
sphere of public spending are of key importance in the second 
stage of the program's implementation. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

