<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vlado Trisic] </F>
  [Text] The enemy offensive on Mount Majevica is not 
abating. What is more, it is becoming increasingly intensive by 
the day. Civilian houses are increasingly being targeted by the 
enemy. According to reports that arrived this afternoon from the 
East Bosnian corps of the army of the Serbian republic, today, 
the 8th day of the offensive, the enemy has fired more than 200 
shells at the Stolice relay station and stepped up 
infantry-artillery attacks on Piperi and Miroslavci, north of 
Lopare, from the direction of Celic. Members of NATO today 
wholeheartedly extended help in the latest Muslim offensive on 
Majevica. They have been carrying out intensive reconnaissance 
flights and breaking the sound barrier by flying low around this 
mountain. Despite the strong attacks, the Serbian positions 
have remained unaltered. As we have learned, there were no 
casualties among the Serbian fighters. As we report, which is 
shortly before 1500, the fighting is still going on. 

</TEXT>

