<H3> <TI>   Opening of Temelin Nuclear Plant Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Opening of Temelin Nuclear Plant Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805174294 Prague LIDOVE NOVINY in Czech 14 May 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> AU1805174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague LIDOVE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by "(dan)": "Temelin Is Behind Schedule"] </F>
  [Text] Temelin--The date for putting into operation the 
first block of the Temelin nuclear power station, originally 
scheduled for the fourth quarter of next year, will probably be 
postponed until mid-1996. In connection with the envisaged 
delay, the timetable for the work was on the agenda of 
yesterday's supervisory meeting held to discuss the Temelin 
nuclear power station project, which was attended by Minister 
Dlouhy. Engineer Petr Karas, chairman of the Czech Energy 
Enterprises board, told LIDOVE NOVINY that one of the reasons 
for postponing the date for bringing in the nuclear fuel is the 
change in the technology, and processing the documentation 
associated with it. "Of course, there are other reasons. For 
example, the government's talks on whether to say yes or no to 
Temelin lasted almost two years, which, naturally, had an 
influence on commencing certain activities," added Eng. Karas. 

</TEXT>

