<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik Sees `Many Difficulties' in Partition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Krajisnik Sees `Many Difficulties' in Partition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805143794 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1805143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The latest Geneva declaration and the division of 
the former Bosnia-Herzegovina into two parts is acceptable for 
the Serbian side in principle, but there will be many 
difficulties concerning the envisaged percentages. This was 
stated for SRNA by Momcilo Krajisnik, chairman of the people's 
assembly of the Serbian republic. I do not want to prejudice 
any solutions, but at this moment I do not see any way of 
satisfying Croatian-Muslim demands, Krajisnik said. 
  The Serbs do not want anyone else's land. We are defending 
our ethnic regions in the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, and 
following this principle, the Serbian side is prepared to give 
up part of the territory that is holding at present, even some 
land that it owns, which amounts to 64 percent, for the benefit 
of creating the compactness of the state, Krajisnik said. 
  For the principle, the Serbs will give up parts of the 
territory, but only up to the percent that will not endanger the 
vital interests of the Serbian people. These interests are the 
definitive separation from the Croats and the Muslims and a 
compact state territory, which above all means a corridor 
through the Posavina region, the chairman of the Serbian 
republic assembly explained, adding that other strategic 
interests of the Serbian people, which cannot be given up at any 
cost, are the ethnic regions along the Una, Drina, and Neretva 
Rivers. 
  The Serbian side has many objections to the Geneva 
declaration, but we are currently ignoring them for the benefit 
of the positive shifts, thus leaving room for ending hostilities 
and searching for a mutually agreed solution, Momcilo Krajisnik 
stressed in his interview with SRNA. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-55709 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu097_p_94001" </HT>


