<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Not To Grant Visa to Zhirinovskiy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Not To Grant Visa to Zhirinovskiy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905144494 Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA in Romanian 17 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1905144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Nord-Est Press report: "Russian Ultranationalist Leader </F>
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy Will Not Receive Entry Visa to Romania"] 
  [Text] On 14 May the leadership of the PNT [National 
Peasant Party]-Lambru, a small political group that withdrew 
from the PNTCD [National Peasant Christian-Democratic Party], 
made public its intention to invite Russian ultranationalist 
leader Vladimir Zhirinovskiy to visit Romania, parliamentary 
sources announced. The reason for this invitation, according to 
the PNT-Lambru, is the fact that the Russian politician is "a 
person who has a thorough knowledge of the true history of 
Romania." Authorized sources at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs 
informed us a few days ago that it is out of the question that 
the Russian extremist can receive an entry visa to Romania. We 
wish to remind our readers that a few months ago the Russian 
leader sketched a "map of Europe" in which Romania is not 
included at all as a state. 

</TEXT>

