<H3> <TI>   Assembly Votes Against Structural Changes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Votes Against Structural Changes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005103794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1014 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by unidentified correspondent on National Assembly </F>
debate on cabinet changes proposed by Prime Minister Lyuben 
Berov at the National Assembly in Sofia -- live] 
  [Text] Today's session of the National Assembly has just 
ended. After the National Assembly rejected the structural 
changes to the cabinet proposed by Prime Minister Lyuben Berov, 
the prime minister declared that he will have to ask for a vote 
of confidence in his cabinet. Under the Constitution, the 
Cabinet has to submit a proposal in writing for such a vote. 

</TEXT>

