<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets With Sejm, Senate Presidia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Sejm, Senate Presidia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005121594 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0953 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 20 May--European Commission President 
Jacques Delors met this morning with members of the Sejm and 
Senate Presidia and with the chairmen of the Sejm Commissions 
for Foreign Affairs and for European Treaty Matters. 
  After the meeting, Jan Borkowski, chairman of the Commission 
for European Treaty Matters, said that the most important issue 
discussed today was a proposal by Polish parliament members for 
Poland to participate in the work of setting up the new European 
Union [EU] institutions that are to emerge after the states of 
Central and East Europe are accepted as members of the 
organization. 
  According to Borkowski, Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy suggested 
during the talks that Poland should gain permanent observer 
status in the European Parliament. Borkowski said Delors agreed 
that an initiative should be taken to enable Poland to cooperate 
in reforming the EU. He added that Poland does not want only to 
be a recipient of EU decisions and to stand outside, but that it 
also wants to contribute to the creation of new structures in 
which it is going to participate in the future. 

</TEXT>

