<H3> <TI>   Crvenkovski: New York Negotiations To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crvenkovski: New York Negotiations To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905155894 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1905155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Crvenkovski Refutes"] </F>
  [Text] In regard to the reports for interruption in the 
[Greek-Macedonian] negotiations, Macedonian Foreign Minister 
Stevo Crvenkovski stated for the Macedonian Radio "nothing was 
offered in New York and the talks focused only on continuation 
of the negotiations. I refuse to comment Greek media 
speculations." Citing the Athens news agency, the Macedonian 
Radio and Television informs of a statement of Crvenkovski on 
chances for a way out of the dead end. But, he said, Macedonia 
[The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia -- FYROM] remains 
firmly on its positions as regarding he name issue. The Greek 
govt representative Venizelos stated his country will also keep 
its point of view on the name of its northern neighbour. 

</TEXT>

