<H3> <TI>   Serbs Report Muslim Offensive Near Brcko </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Report Muslim Offensive Near Brcko </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905201494 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1708 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, May 19 (TANJUG) -- Moslem forces on 
Thursday morning followed strong artillery fire with major 
infantry attacks on Serb positions west of Brcko (northeast 
Bosnia), but were repelled by the Bosnian Serb Army, the Bosnian 
Serb Army Press Centre in Brcko said on Thursday. On Wednesday 
evening the Moslems launched another offensive in Brcko by 
opening mortar fire on Serb positions five km to the west of 
this town. Intensive Moslem massing of forces has also been 
reported in the Sava River valley where the Moslems are bringing 
reinforcements from the region of Tuzla, Moslem-controlled town 
south of Brcko. 
  According to Bosnian Serb sources, two brigades of the First 
Moslem Army Corps have been transferred from the Sarajevo area. 
The Moslems continue violating the ceasefire agreement in the 
region of Sarajevo by opening strong sniper fire on the Serb 
settlements of Ilidza and Grbavica and the Local Rehabilitation 
Institute, the Bosnian Serb Army said. 
  Along the entire front line close to Orasje, Bosnian Croat 
forces (HVO) on Wednesday opened infantry and artillery fire on 
Serb positions. Troop movements towards Serb positions were 
also recorded on the left bank of the Sava in the territory of 
Croatia, as reported by U.N. monitors stationed in Brcko, the 
Bosnian Serb Army sources said. 
  A general artillery and infantry attack launched by the 
Moslems on Wednesday along the Serb defence lines on Mt. Vlasic 
(central Bosnia) continued on Thursday, TANJUG reported from 
Zvornik citing Bosnian Serb Army sources. 

</TEXT>

