<F P=106> [Article by "otk": "Will the Quality of Teaching Slovak Be </F>
Improved?"] 
  [Text] Bratislava--A new objection to the budget of the 
Ministry of Education has emerged in the ethnically mixed 
territories. Under the ministry's pedagogical and 
organizational instructions and teaching curriculums, an extra 
one to two hours of Slovak language and conversation [per week] 
are to be added in schools with a non-Slovak language of 
instruction. Moreover, preference is to be given to the 
division of classes during Slovak language lessons. Lubomir 
Harach, minister of education and science, informed us that the 
ministry has released from its budget a reserve of 100 million 
korunas to secure education [in the Slovak language] in the 
ethnically mixed territories. 

