<H3> <TI>   PHARE Program Allots 60 Million ECU's </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PHARE Program Allots 60 Million ECU's </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905191194 Prague CESKY DENIK in Czech 18 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1905191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CESKY DENIK </F>
<F P=105>  Czech </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Bohumil Srajer: "A Signature That Has Brought Us </F>
Closer to Europe"] 
  [Text] The PHARE [Economic Reconstruction Aid for Poland 
and Hungary] guiding program, which specifies priority areas for 
European Union [EU] assistance to the Czech Republic, was signed 
by Deputy Foreign Minister Pavel Bratinka and Leopoldo Giunti, 
the EU Commission's emissary to the Czech Republic, in Cernin 
Palace [in Prague] yesterday. 
  The program covers new trends in cooperation between the 
Czech Republic and the EU. The principal change is the PHARE 
shift from only technical assistance to support for specific 
projects, particularly in transportation and the environment. 
Great attention will also be paid to the preparation of Czech 
institutions for future integration into EU structures. 
According to Pavel Bratinka, the key sphere is private 
business, with an emphasis on restructuring industry and 
developing small and medium-size enterprises. Another sphere on 
which PHARE will concentrate is education. The project also 
intends to assist in reinforcing the social net. It is expected 
that a total of 60 million ECU's (approximately 2.04 billion 
korunas) will be spent on new obligations of the PHARE program. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

