other parties' candidates in the second round of parliamentary 
elections from May 8 to 29. 
  A Smallholder alliance with the Hungarian Democratic Forum 
[MDF] is out of the question: Smallholders feel that after the 
first round (May 8), MDF deputies with seats in parliament from 
party lists are closer to the liberal Alliance of Free Democrats 
than to the Smallholders. 
  However, the FKGP is discussing possible long-term 
cooperation with the Christian Democrats, FKGP Deputy Chairman 
and campaign chief Mrs. Nagy G. Agnes Maczo told reporters in 
Budapest on Thursday. 

