<H3> <TI>   MDF's Lezsak Fears `Constitutional Dictatorship' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MDF's Lezsak Fears `Constitutional Dictatorship' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905173894 Budapest MTI in English 1527 GMT 19 May 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 19 May (MTI) -- "The Hungarian Democratic 
Forum [MDF] has quickly recovered after the shock which the May 
8 election result caused to its voters and organizers," MDF 
acting chairman Sandor Lezsak told the party's news conference 
in Budapest on Thursday. He said he believes broad cooperation 
between conservative forces could obstruct a Socialist-Liberal 
majority in the new parliament. 
  According to Lezsak, many people want to vote on May 29 for 
fear of an overwhelming ruling power leading to autocratic rule 
and a constitutional dictatorship. On June 4, the MDF's 
National Board will look into the reasons behind the party's 
poor election performance. It will also decide whether to 
discuss past and current affairs with delegates of the 8th 
National Convention, or to elect new delegates, and select a 
date for the next national meeting sometime before October. 

</TEXT>

