<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Romania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iliescu Rules Out Return to Communism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iliescu Rules Out Return to Communism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905124194 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 0918 GMT 19 May 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 19/5/1994 -- A return to 
communist regime "is no longer possible. The old totalitarian 
regime has been demolished. It is a dialectical process and it 
is our duty to adjust to other rules, the rules of the end of 
the 20th century, when the tendency to integrate all national 
economies into the world economy is a dominant," President Ion 
Iliescu stated during a meeting at the Oradea Municipality City 
Hall. 
  President Iliescu admitted that adjustment to the new 
situation has generated severe social issues, but pointed out 
that the causes of such phenomenon must be traced down and 
eliminated, rejecting the wish of some to return to the old 
totalitarian rule. President Iliescu pleaded for dialogue as a 
means to solve most of the social issues: "It is good to listen 
to each other and to learn from the experience of each other. 
This is the fundamental element that rules our democracy, for a 
society keeps developing when all human potentials are being 
capitalised," Iliescu said. 
  The meeting at Oradea City Hall took place after a visit 
paid 
by President Ion Iliescu to the Bihor County. "It has been a day 
of fruitful contacts and dialogues that were beneficial for me, 
for I had the possibility to directly get acquainted with the 
issues confronting people and with their thoughts," President 
Iliescu told a ROMPRES editor. "As a general feature, I would 
mention the people's concern for the really big issues 
confronting our economy, such as the financial blockage, 
inflation and unemployment, as well as their wish for an 
economic revival." 
  President Ion Iliescu's fact-finding trip is to include on 
Thursday the Satu Mare County. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

