<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Fierce' Assembly Debate Over Census Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Fierce' Assembly Debate Over Census Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1405165494 Tirana ATA in English 0821 GMT 14 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1405165494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 14 (ATA) -- A fierce debate is 
continuing in the Macedonian [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM] parliament in regard to the census. 
Referring to sources from Skopje, the Albanian Television 
reported that the Albanian deputies requested on May 13, that 
the document of the citizenship be presented during the census 
because the Interior Ministry is not able to provide them; 
Albanians who work abroad be treated as citizens of The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia and also be included in the 
general number of the population, not in special categories. 
  The Albanian deputies requested also that several Albanian 
people be employed at the Statistical Enterprise and a formulary 
sample should remain at the families who have been registered. 
  The amendments of the Albanians deputies did not find 
support 
and caused uncontrolled reactions by the Macedonian deputies. 
According to the Macedonian deputies, these amendments request 
the legalization of the Albanians who have come from Kosova, 
Serbia, and Albania. The Macedonian deputies supported 
indirectly the thesis that the Albanians of Macedonia have 
Macedonian citizenship and should be declared as Macedonians. 
The parliament stopped its proceedings because of the tense 
atmosphere created by partial and dissuading discussion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

