<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Approves Census Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Approves Census Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005090094 Tirana ATA in English 0818 GMT 20 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2005090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana May 20 (ATA) -- The parliament of The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM], approved the Law on the 
Census of Population, after a long debate and also in the 
presence of the experts of the Council of Europe, reports the 
Albanian TV correspondent, from Skopje. The census will be 
conducted from June 21 to July 1st of this year. 
  The commission of the Council of Europe that is staying in 
Skopje, met with the Albanian representatives and the VMRO 
[Internal Macedonian Revolutionary Organization] group, 
regarding the draft law on population census, before the holding 
the parliament's session. The content of the talks is not yet 
known but the chairman of the experts' team, Vener Hog [name as 
received], declared that they support the draft law and their is 
no room for any change in it. The law, said he, is a 
compromising setting, where each side wins something, but none 
of them all. 
  The Albanians declared that they support the general census 
of population only under the international supervision. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

