<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Soldiers on Border Ban Farming Work </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Soldiers on Border Ban Farming Work </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805195294 Tirana ATA in English 1016 GMT 18 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1805195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, May 18 (ATA) -- A considerable number of 
Serb soldiers are deployed recently in the border area between 
Albania and Kosova so banning the Albanian farmers from using 
the pasture land. They have declared it "forbidden area," 
because it is near the border zone. The army has blocked the 
roads that lead to the pasture land and conducts a severe 
search, prohibiting so the free pass of people. 
  Against such measures, have reacted the Albanian political 
subjects of Decan commune and has appealed to the farmers to be 
cautious not to fall into the trap of the Serb militaries. 

</TEXT>

