<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Party Leader Rejects Dialogue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Party Leader Rejects Dialogue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1905162494 Tirana ATA in English 1210 GMT 19 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1905162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prishtina, May 19 (ATA) -- Mirko Cupioi, chairman 
of the regional council of criminal Arkan's party, based in 
Prishtina, declared in the newspaper JEDINSTVO that "one can not 
even think of dialogue with the Albanians." According to him, 
the Kosova status will be negotiated with no one, less so "with 
those residing in the foreign land," alluding to the ethnic 
Albanians of Kosova. Further on, he reveals that the Serb Unity 
Party has a wide and detailed program on Kosova, which predicts 
the fast establishment of national parity with the settling of 
500 thousand Serbs in Kosova and the expulsion of 465 thousand 
Albanians to Albania. 
  On the other hand, the leaders of Seselj's radicals in 
Kosova, Miodrag Jevric, declares in the newspaper BORBA that the 
participants of national minorities should not be provided with 
weapons during military service, whereas those who do not 
respond to the order for military service "can buy the military 
term" at 5,000 U.S. dollars. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

