<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Yugoslavia, Kosovo </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Serbian Military Authorities' Execute Albanian </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Serbian Military Authorities' Execute Albanian </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805183194 Tirana ATA in English 0836 GMT 15 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1805183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 15 (ATA) -- Albanian soldier Shaban 
Bajrami has been killed by two bullets fired into his mouth 
under charges of having killed two Serbian solders in the 
Mladenovc garrison in Serbia. Serbian military authorities said 
that Bajrami has been liquidated because he fled and did not 
accept to surrender. Information Council of the branch of the 
Party for Democratic Action in Medvegje reported these days 
about the killing of Shaban Bajrami from the village Kapit of 
Medvegje and described the grave situation of the Albanian 
population prior and after Bajrami was killed. 
  Reports from the council throw light on some facts which 
show 
that Shaban Bajrami has not killed the two Serbian soldiers. 
Reports also confirm that Shaban Bajrami has not been executed 
in the village Ratare of Smederevska Pallanka, as Serbian 
military authorities has reported. 
  On the basis of testimonies by Bajrami's family members, the 
council reports that Shaban Bajrami was shot with two bullets in 
the mouth. His father confirmed this after he saw his son's 
corpse when asked to carry it from Belgrade. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

