<H3> <TI>   `Albanologist Institute' Resumes Activities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Albanologist Institute' Resumes Activities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1805191194 Tirana ATA in English 1027 GMT 18 May 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1805191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, May 18 (ATA) -- The Prishtina Albanologist 
Institute violently banned by the Serbian authorities on March 
8, 1994, resumed today its activity in a private house, Behlul 
Jashari, the ATA correspondent in Prishtina, reported today. 
The institute director, Dr. Sadri Fetiu, said in an interview 
with ATA, that the institute will publish this year 32 
scientific works. 
  Mr. Fetiu said: "The greatest difficulty is the isolation of 
the institute from the scientific and intellectual world 
especially with the scientific institutions of Albania because 
of the obstacles put by the Serbian authorities who do not allow 
the world literature to pass to the Prishtina Library and vice 
versa. 

</TEXT>

