<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   KNSB Calls Off Strike Action During Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KNSB Calls Off Strike Action During Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005172294 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1600 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Executive Committee of the KNSB [Confederation 
of Independent Trade Unions in Bulgaria] decided today to call 
off mass strike actions until parliament reaches a final 
decision on the fate of the Lyuben Berov cabinet, but the KNSB 
structures are to remain ready to strike. 
  The protests that are planned to begin on 25 May in various 
parts of the country are to be supported by KNSB union 
federations and regional structures. This decision was adopted 
after the Executive Committee had reached the view that at the 
moment no parliamentary majority exists and that the country has 
no legitimate government able to adopt responsible decisions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

