<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozloduy Station Shuts Down Reactor Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozloduy Station Shuts Down Reactor Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005152494 Sofia DUMA in Bulgarian 17 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2005152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia DUMA </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Duma Press" report] </F>
  [Text] The Kozloduy Nuclear Power Station has announced 
that the No. 1 reactor unit has been shut down because of a 
minor defect, namely poor flow in bleeding air from the No. 1 
main circulating pump. The unit was shut down on instructions 
from the central operations room. There are no changes in the 
radiation situation in the country. The defect will be repaired 
by the end of the week. Even with the No. 1 reactor out of 
operation, the nuclear power station is producing 1,520 
megawatts, so the national grid will not be affected. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

