<H3> <TI>   Serbs Claim NATO Supporting Majevica Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Claim NATO Supporting Majevica Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2105150794 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1300 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2105150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Vlado Trisic from Mt. Majevica front] </F>
  [Text] Muslim forces, supported by the international 
forces, are today again attacking Serbian positions on Mt. 
Majevica with increasing intensity. On two occasions, at 0500 
and 0800, NATO planes made a low altitude flyover, a mere 100 
meters above the woods, and provoked Serbian defense forces, 
which did not respond to the provocations. This seems to have 
been an introduction to yet another attack of the Muslim forces, 
who, from strongholds in Donje Hrasno, the region of the Stolice 
transmitter, and Banj Brdo, showered the area with shells of 
various caliber, at the same time regrouping for infantry 
assaults. 
  The information service of the republic of Srpska army east 
Bosnian corps this afternoon announced that the Muslim forces 
were carrying out an artillery and infantry attack in the area 
of Jablanica and Piper, north of Lopari. The Muslims from 
Horozovina -- southeast of Tuzla -- are targeting ambulances and 
Serbian positions in Banj Brdo with a Broving gun. As we report 
this, and it is now just after 1400, NATO planes have again 
begun carrying out provocations on Mt. Majevica [words 
indistinct] did not cause the Serbian troops to waver in their 
goal to defend their territory from the latest Muslim aggression. 

</TEXT>

