<H3> <TI>   Outlines Talk With Delors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Outlines Talk With Delors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105090094 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0500 
GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105090094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>
<F P=105>  Polish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] At a news conference, Prime Minister 
Pawlak pointed out the following problems: 
  [Begin Pawlak recording] We had the opportunity to brief 
President Delors on Poland's political and economic situation. 
We told him Poland puts the goal of integration with the EU 
first, but is not neglecting other actions streamlining 
cooperation, particularly regional cooperation, chiefly with the 
Czech Republic, Slovakia, Hungary, and the CEFTA [Central 
European Free Trade Agreement]. We have intensified our work in 
this sphere. A very important part of the talks concerned the 
infrastructure in the broad sense, including communications, but 
also concerning the information infrastructure. These are the 
areas that will decide the future, on the conditions for the 
economy and our society's development. This enables us to look 
with greater faith at Europe's future. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

