<H3> <TI>   Serbs Seal Off Pristina Market, Make Arrests </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Seal Off Pristina Market, Make Arrests </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005203094 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Reports from Prishtina confirm that at about 1100 
today, large Serbian forces blocked all entries and exits to the 
market of the capital of the Republic of Kosova. Thousands of 
people were in the market simply trading, the majority preparing 
for the [Muslim] festival of Bairam. This Serbian police 
operation lasted for more than four hours. It is reported that 
the Albanian traders had more than 500 German marks stolen. In 
addition to this thievery, the Serbian police arrested many 
young Albanians and sent them to the command headquarters of the 
Serbian security bodies in Prishtina. 

</TEXT>

