<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Skopje Air Base To Be Adapted for Civilian Traffic </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Skopje Air Base To Be Adapted for Civilian Traffic </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105093994 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 0801 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Skopje, 21 May (TANJUG) -- The Skopje air base 
Petrovec will soon become a mostly civilian airport. At a 
meeting with the president 20 May, representatives of the 
Macedonian Transport and Defense Ministries agreed that two out 
of three airstrips will be used for civilian purposes -- one for 
passenger and the other for cargo air traffic. After the 
departure of the JNA [Yugoslav People's Army], the Petrovec air 
base was mostly taken over by the army of the recently formed 
state. This impeded development of civilian air traffic, while 
the military section of the airport was insufficiently 
exploited. Modernization plans have been announced for next 
year, primarily the reconstruction of the runway and signaling 
system. 

</TEXT>

