  [Excerpt] The 14th session of the Chamber of Counties is 
expected to resume within an hour. Josip Manolic is expected to 
finally resign at this session. A new speaker and new deputy 
speakers of the chamber will also be elected. This is what the 
Croatian Democratic Union [HDZ] deputies have been discussing 
since 1000, that is 1100 [as heard], in state president and 
party chairman Tudjman's residence. 
  Opposition leaders, too, are talking behind closed doors at 
the Croatian Assembly. Both sides are outlining their strategy 
for implementing an interparty agreement. The opposition must 
come up with their candidates for deputy speakers in the Chamber 
of Counties by 1400. As yet, no one is willing to make any 
official statement. This is why we can reveal only an unofficial 
and unconfirmed piece of information: the deputy speaker posts 
in the Chamber of Counties should be allocated to the Croatian 
Liberal Democratic Party and the Croatian Peasants' Party. 
